## Production Environment Variables Template

## Server Configuration
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=production

## Database
# Use MongoDB Atlas connection string for production
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster.mongodb.net/eventsnap?retryWrites=true&w=majority

## JWT Configuration
# Generate a strong secret key for production (use openssl rand -base64 32)
JWT_SECRET=your_production_jwt_secret_change_this_in_production

## Cloudinary Configuration
# Get these from your Cloudinary dashboard: https://cloudinary.com/console
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloudinary_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_cloudinary_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_cloudinary_api_secret

## Frontend Configuration (REQUIRED - NO LOCALHOST ALLOWED)
# ⚠️ CRITICAL: Replace with your ACTUAL Vercel deployment URL
# ⚠️ Example: https://eventsnap.vercel.app
# ⚠️ NO localhost, NO IPs, NO tunnels allowed
# ⚠️ This MUST be your public production domain
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-app-name.vercel.app

## Email Configuration (Gmail)
# Use your actual Gmail credentials or configure another email service
GMAIL_USER=your_email@gmail.com
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=your_gmail_app_password

## Security Notes:
# 1. Never commit this file to version control
# 2. Use different secrets for development and production
# 3. Keep your API keys secure and rotate them regularly
# 4. In production platforms (Render, Heroku, etc.), set these as environment variables
# 5. Make sure FRONTEND_URL matches your Vercel deployment exactly
